<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Lind on 05-28-2002 03:22 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[b]  I Think this is the point.  Druids have become gods of anything in the simple zones where people would rake in exp and require minimal healing.[/b]
 
  NO!  Any group that a druid can be primary healer in is BETTER OFF without the druid (or cleric.)  Druid's sustained damage output even with moonfire is paltry compared to a meleer and their healing so bad that they just can't help a group kill enough to pay for the XP they're sucking.  Even wizards throwing nothing but Ice Spears are nothing more than XP leechs in xp groups.
 
[b]Now Verant has turned around and designed a great zone bringing back the necessity of a cleric for grouping, and you berate it because you can't cut the healing mustard as you feel entitled to.[/b]
 
  The group needs a cleric, fine.  No problem.  Don't need a ranger, don't need an SK, don't need a monk, don't need a wizard, don't need a druid, don't need a mage, but NEEDING a cleric is okay?  No, it isn't.
 
  That aside, you find a cleric, every 6th person on the server is a cleric anyway because you need them, and you go there and... guess what?  As a druid you can't backup heal because the mobs hit for 400 and your feeble heal spells suck, so you don't even try.  You use moonfire which is just as efficient as Garrison's or Elnerik's and guess what, you and the wizard at the end of the night did... the exact same damage, and half the damage of a meleer.  i.e. punt the druid, punt the wizard, grab 2 more meleer and you'd have killed 25% more, gotten 25% more xp.
 
[b]You pay a price for being capable of doing a little of everything.  As a specialist I ought to be more powerful in certain circumstances.[/b]
 
  Clerics are no more specialists than anyone else.  Druids no more a generalist than anyone else.  Give druids fear, atone, lull, rez, da, the word AEs, and buff heals and I'll agree with you.

</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
